        <h3 style="font-size:16px; margin-bottom:8px; letter-spacing:0;">Why does my breaker keep tripping?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--steel); font-size:14.5px;">A breaker that trips repeatedly is usually a sign of an overloaded circuit, a short, or a failing breaker itself. It's worth having a licensed electrician check it before it becomes a bigger problem.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--offwhite); border:1px solid #e6e2d8; border-radius:10px; padding:22px 26px;">
        <h3 style="font-size:16px; margin-bottom:8px; letter-spacing:0;">How much does a panel upgrade cost?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--steel); font-size:14.5px;">Panel upgrade costs vary based on your home's size, current panel age, and amperage needs. We offer free estimates and financing options to make it manageable — call or text 412-424-9588 for a quote specific to your home.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--offwhite); border:1px solid #e6e2d8; border-radius:10px; padding:22px 26px;">
        <h3 style="font-size:16px; margin-bottom:8px; letter-spacing:0;">Can I install an EV charger at my house?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--steel); font-size:14.5px;">In most cases, yes. Your home's panel may need to support the additional load, which we can assess during a free estimate. We handle EV charger installs for homes throughout Penn Hills, Pittsburgh, and Monroeville.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--offwhite); border:1px solid #e6e2d8; border-radius:10px; padding:22px 26px;">
        <h3 style="font-size:16px; margin-bottom:8px; letter-spacing:0;">Why are my lights flickering?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--steel); font-size:14.5px;">Flickering lights can point to a loose connection, an overloaded circuit, or an aging panel. It's one of the more common reasons homeowners call us — better to get it checked than wait.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:var(--offwhite); border:1px solid #e6e2d8; border-radius:10px; padding:22px 26px;">
        <h3 style="font-size:16px; margin-bottom:8px; letter-spacing:0;">Do I need a licensed electrician, or can I DIY?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--steel); font-size:14.5px;">Most electrical work requires a permit and inspection, and mistakes can be a fire or safety hazard. A licensed electrician ensures the work is done to code and your home stays safe and insurable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

